org.rdkit.knime.nodes.chemicaltransformation

Class RDKitChemicalTransformationNodeModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • NodeModel
      • org.rdkit.knime.nodes.AbstractRDKitNodeModel
        • org.rdkit.knime.nodes.AbstractRDKitCalculatorNodeModel
          • org.rdkit.knime.nodes.chemicaltransformation.RDKitChemicalTransformationNodeModel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RDKitObjectCleaner

    public class RDKitChemicalTransformationNodeModel
extends AbstractRDKitCalculatorNodeModel
    This class implements the node model of the RDKitChemicalTransformation node providing calculations based on the open source RDKit library. Transforms a structure into another structure by applying several reactions provided as SMARTS values.
    Author:
    Manuel Schwarze

      • createInputDataInfos

        protected InputDataInfo[] createInputDataInfos(int inPort,
                                               DataTableSpec inSpec)
                                        throws InvalidSettingsException
        This implementation generates input data info object for the input mol column and connects it with the information coming from the appropriate setting model. This method needs to be implemented by a concrete node to generate InputDataInfo objects for each input column for all input tables. To find the proper column, the concrete node implementation must pass in the appropriate setting model of the column name into the constructor of the InputDataInfo class.
        Specified by:
        createInputDataInfos in class AbstractRDKitNodeModel
        Parameters:
        inPort - The port number of the input table to create input data objects for.
        inSpec - The table specification of the input table. Can be null.
        Returns:
        An array of info objects for all columns used as input for the passed table. Should not return null. If no input columns are used from the passed table, it should return an empty array.
        Throws:
        InvalidSettingsException - Thrown, if the current settings or the spec of the input table will make it impossible to process the data.

        protected DataTableSpec getOutputTableSpec(int outPort,

      • createOutputFactories

        protected AbstractRDKitCellFactory[] createOutputFactories(int outPort,
                                                           DataTableSpec inSpec)
                                                    throws InvalidSettingsException
        This method needs to be implemented by a concrete node to generate cell factories for all output tables. As there can be more than one factory specified to generate cells for a table, it returns for one output port an array of factories. However, usually only one element will be contained in this array.
        Specified by:
        createOutputFactories in class AbstractRDKitCalculatorNodeModel
        Parameters:
        outPort - The port number of the output table to create factories for.
        inSpec - Specification of the table to be merged with new columns that will be generated by the factories. Can be null.
        Returns:
        An array of factory objects. Should not return null. If no factories are used, it should return an empty array.
        Throws:
        InvalidSettingsException - Thrown, if creation of output factories fails.

      • createColumnRearranger

        protected ColumnRearranger createColumnRearranger(int outPort,
                                                  DataTableSpec inSpec)
                                           throws InvalidSettingsException
        Creates a column rearranger based on all cell factories that are delivered by a call to #createOutputFactories(int)). These factories (usually there is just one) implement the logic to calculate new cells based on the input defined by the input data info objects delivered by a call to AbstractRDKitNodeModel.createInputDataInfos(DataTableSpec[]). This implementation removes additionally the compound source column, if specified in the settings.
        Overrides:
        createColumnRearranger in class AbstractRDKitCalculatorNodeModel
        Parameters:
        outPort - The output port of the node the column rearranger shall be created for. This value is used to create the output factories - a call is made to #createOutputFactories(int) with this outPort id.
        inSpec - The specification of the table the result column rearranger shall be based on. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        Column Rearranger for the specified input table.
        Throws:
        InvalidSettingsException - Thrown, if invalid settings are encountered while creating and gathering all necessary information in order to create the column rearranger object.

      • cleanupIntermediateResults

        protected void cleanupIntermediateResults()
        This method gets called at the very end of the node execution. It is called also after the user canceled the execution. It can be overridden to cleanup all intermediate results, e.g. arrays, which have been created to pass over values from pre-processing to processing to post-processing steps. Always check for null before calling cleanup functionality on resources. They may have never instancianted, if the user canceled before the resource was created. By default, this method is not doing anything. Exceptions thrown from this method will be caught and logged as a warning, but will not have any effect on the process flow.
        Overrides:
        cleanupIntermediateResults in class AbstractRDKitNodeModel
